<HR>


<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME=fifteen>Fifteen Common Sense Tool Categories </A></H2>
With input from the Federal community, work has begun on several of the tool categories, however we welcome data and suggestions on all categories.
<UL>
<LI><B>Leadership</B> - Tools used by leaders to inspire accomplishment and innovation in the workforce by their vision and their behavior.  Tools that encourage and reward risk-taking.

<LI><A HREF="toolcom.html"><B>Communication</B></A> -  Tools for employees to effectively express their goals and values to peers, customers, and all stakeholders.  Tools that sharpen listening skills.   

<LI><A HREF="/custserv/index.html"><B>Customer-Focus</B></A> -  Tools to empower and energize service providers to meet and exceed  internal and external customer expectations.

<LI><B>Innovation and Learning</B>-  Tools to ensure that continuous learning becomes an integral part of the workplace to address contemporary demands and capitalize on future trends.  

<LI><B>Organizational Design</B> -  Tools to prudently reshape organizations so that they can meet the demands of their customers or enterprise. 

<LI><B>Partnerships</B> -  Tools that encourage and solidify relationships across traditional organizational or business lines to improve products or the delivery of services to customers.

<LI><B>Financial Management</B> -  Tools, including budget and financial controls, that create fiscal accountability to the American taxpayers without diminishing customer service.

<LI><A HREF="acquisit.html"><B>Procurement and Acquisition</B></A>- Tools that obtain needed goods and services timely, fairly, and at best price. 

<LI><A HREF="/library/papers/bkgrd/cover.html"><B>Strategic Planning and Performance Measurement</B></A> - Tools that establish organizational goals that are consistent with agency mission and can be measured for anticipated results.

<LI><B>Empowered Teams</B> -  Tools that strategically align skills within agencies to address common goals and to be jointly accountable for outcomes 

<LI><B>New Technology</B> -  Tools that ensure that automation and technology continually support organizational goals, customer expectations, and employee needs. 

<LI><B>Re-Engineering and Streamlining</B> -  Tools that practice change management and embed  efficiency, innovation, and customer service into the agency culture.

<LI><B><A HREF="#human">Human Resource Development</A></B>  - Tools that empower employees and create partnerships with management.  Tools that create a family-friendly work site.

<LI><B>Legal Support</B> -  Tools that eliminate burdensome regulations.  Tools that create alternatives  to resource-consuming litigation.

<LI><A HREF="admin.html"><B>Administrative Services</B></A>  - Tools that free employees from non value-added process requirements so they are freed to focus of product quality and customer service.

</UL><P>
<HR>
