<HEAD>
<TITLE>	NPR: Focus of the Second Phase</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<P>
<P><B>_________________________________________________________________________________</B><BR>
Document Name<B>:	</B><B>NPR: Focus of the Second Phase</B><BR>
Date:	<B>		</B><B>12/01/94</B><BR>
Owner:	<B>		</B><B>National Performance Review</B>		<BR>

<B>_________________________________________________________________________________</B><BR>
** NATIONAL PERFORMANCE REVIEW: **<BR>

<P>** FOCUS OF THE SECOND PHASE    **<BR>

<P>** December 1994                **  <BR>

<P>            <BR>

<P>President Clinton and Vice President Gore have<BR>

<P>announced a second performance review, beginning<BR>

<P>today. This new review -- to create a leaner, not a<BR>

<P>meaner government -- will expand on the first effort<BR>

<P>in the following ways:<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>The first phase of NPR cut back to basics, but we<BR>

<P>can do even better. The second phase of NPR will:<BR>

<P>            <BR>

<P>- eliminate remnants of yesterday's government that<BR>

<P>  just don't make sense in today's world, and<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>- restructure things that can be better run as a<BR>

<P>  business instead of a bureaucracy.<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>The first phase of NPR devolved authority to state<BR>

<P>and local government, but we can do even better. The<BR>

<P>second phase of NPR will identify things that can be<BR>

<P>done better by:<BR>

<P>            <BR>

<P>-- the states and communities involved. and<BR>

<P>-- individual Americans<BR>

<P>                 <BR>

<P>The first phase of NPR improved the regulatory<BR>

<P>process, but we can do even better. The second phase<BR>

<P>of NPR will undertake a major reinvention of the way<BR>

<P>the federal government regulates and how it enforces<BR>

<P>its regulations.<BR>

<P>             <BR>

<P>We will continue to deliver on the promises we made<BR>

<P>in the first phase of the National Performance<BR>

<P>Review.<BR>

<P>
<PRE>

</PRE>
