<TITLE>	Putting It Together: NPR Phase II</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<P>
<P><B>_________________________________________________________________________________</B><BR>
Document Name<B>:	</B><B>Putting It Together: NPR Phase II</B><BR>
Date:	<B>		</B><B>02/01/95</B><BR>
Owner:	<B>		</B><B>National Performance Review</B>		<BR>

<B>_________________________________________________________________________________</B><BR>

<P>** National Performance Review:   Phase II **<BR>

<P>** Putting It Together                     **<BR>

<P>** February 1995                           **<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>***************************************<BR>

<P>** Executive Summary of NPR Phase II **<BR>

<P>***************************************<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>1. Agency Restructuring Initiative<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>~ Agencies will create teams to develop options to<BR>

<P>  present to the NPR Phase II Steering Committee,<BR>

<P>  and to the Vice President and OMB Director. <BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>~ Five advisory teams, aligned with OMB's RMOs, will<BR>

<P>  be created for large agencies and substantively<BR>

<P>  related small agencies.  A separate small agency<BR>

<P>  advisory team will provide input into the 5 lead<BR>

<P>  advisory teams. <BR>

<P>       <BR>

<P>-- NPR cross-cutting teams will provide ideas and<BR>

<P>   technical assistance.  <BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>-- Timetable will vary, depending on agency; most<BR>

<P>   will be completed by mid-March (see calendar).<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>2.  Federalism Initiative<BR>

<P>   <BR>

<P>~ Team comprised of OMB/NPR/White House/Treasury<BR>

<P>  staffs will develop overall guiding principles and<BR>

<P>  support agency teams.<BR>

<P>  <BR>

<P>~ Following these principles, agencies may develop<BR>

<P>  proposals to realign federal, state, and local<BR>

<P>  responsibilities as part of their restructuring<BR>

<P>  efforts.<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>~ Conduct outreach to get ideas and reactions from<BR>

<P>  Congress, state-local partners, academia, and<BR>

<P>  others to help provide ideas to agency-based<BR>

<P>  teams.<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>3.  Regulatory Reinvention Initiative<BR>

<P>   <BR>

<P>~ Overall goal is to consider different models for<BR>

<P>  achieving regulatory objectives with an emphasis<BR>

<P>  on minimizing federal governmental intrusion and<BR>

<P>  creating a customer service orientation.<BR>

<P>~ Organize a series of seminars for the VP focusing<BR>

<P>  on major regulatory policy areas and crosscutting<BR>

<P>  issues.<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>-- OVP/NPR staff work with OMB to support agency/<BR>

<P>   White House policy council teams.<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>-- Teams will be formed to put together specific<BR>

<P>   proposals.<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>4.  Implement Phase I of NPR <BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>~ Measure progress toward achieving the goals set in<BR>

<P>  Customer Service Standards<BR>

<P>~ Create a &quot;Virtual Department of Business&quot; among<BR>

<P>  the 55 agencies that work with the business<BR>

<P>  community to better serve them. <BR>

<P>~ Adopt Public Service Reform legislation.<BR>

<P>~ Continue electonic communications with federal<BR>

<P>  employees through NetResults<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>5.  Crosscutting Teams<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>~ Conduct research and provide ideas and technical<BR>

<P>  help to agency and advisory teams: <BR>

<P>  <BR>

<P>  -- Privatization and Franchising<BR>

<P>  -- Streamlining and Field Structure<BR>

<P>  -- Individual Empowerment (e.g., vouchers)<BR>

<P>  -- Subsidy identification<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>6.  Legislative-Executive Branch Relations<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>~ Track legislation from NPR Phase I<BR>

<P>~ Coordinate the introduction of legislation<BR>

<P>~ Develop communication mechanism with congressional<BR>

<P>  staff regarding timing of the submission of NPR<BR>

<P>  Phase II proposals<BR>

